" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jrc1665702631553.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jrc1665702631553.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jrc1665702631553.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jrc1665702631553\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\"> CommandButton\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__commandbutton_368734\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by\n      clicking the button. </p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__p_d112556e1_d112557e1_d112558e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__fig_w2882ab1b5b3b1_w2883ab1b5b3_w2884ab1b5_w2885ab1\">\n<img alt=\"CommandButton widget\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/commandbtn.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div><p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akm1704707836734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akm1704707836734.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\">Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__table_d13370e1_d13371e1_d13372e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Logical widget name:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">CommandButton</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Maps to physical widget:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ucmdbutton</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default definition: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CommandButton=ucmdbutton(tooltip=on;font=buttonfont;actOnEachClick=on)</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported triggers and properties: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nnf1665702631473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nnf1665702631473.html\" title=\"The ucmdbutton widget is a button that the user can click to initiate an action. It is a field-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">ucmdbutton</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Use for: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Static or control fields (as defined by the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Static</span>\n                        and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Is Control</span> properties) of type String.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\"> Supports Accessibility? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\"> Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more\n                     information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"abr1688541158363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/abr1688541158363.html\" title=\"Uniface exposes the UI of generated Windows desktop applications to screen readers and automation tools for a number of widgets. By exposing the underlying infrastructure, screen readers and automated testing tools can target supported UI elements, and retrieve information regarding their name, value, and status. For these purposes, a mixture of two different technologies has been used - UI Automation and MSAA (Microsoft Active Accessibility).\">Accessibility</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__topic_d79742e1_d79743e1_d79744e1_d79745e1_d79746e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d522531e195\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__p_d112562e1_d112563e1_d112564e1\">The specified action is defined in the Detail\n            trigger of the button field. Because this field is not used for data input, it is\n            usually defined as a static or control field.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__note_w2886ab1b5b7b5_w2887ab1b5b7_w2888ab1b5_w2889ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> Uniface provides\n            templates for command buttons that perform common actions such as retrieving and storing\n            data, adding and removing entity occurrences, and more.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jrc1665702631553__p_d112565e1_d112566e1_d112567e1\">By default, the CommandButton follows the Windows\n            look and feel. If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Representation</span> property is set to\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">Uniface</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">Header</code>, the appearance is different. For\n            more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"soa1665702631628.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/soa1665702631628.html\" title=\"The UnifaceButton is a logical widget for a button that can be styled using colors and images. It supports properties that are not available for other command buttons.\">UnifaceButton</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gaf1665702631801.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gaf1665702631801.html\" title=\"The HeaderButton is a logical widget for styling a button to look like a column heading.\">HeaderButton</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxc1665702631725.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Defining Command Buttons</a><p>Command buttons enable the user to perform specific actions. They should only be used in form components, not in reports.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qvt1665702616238.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>KeyPadEnterAccess</a><p>Specifies whether the keypad Enter key is routed through the keyboard translation table for command buttons.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "CommandButton Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 CommandButton The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button. For more information, see Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity . Table 1. Widget Overview Logical widget name: CommandButton Maps to physical widget: ucmdbutton Default definition: CommandButton=ucmdbutton(tooltip=on;font=buttonfont;actOnEachClick=on) Supported triggers and properties: See ucmdbutton . Use for: Static or control fields (as defined by the Is Static and Is Control properties) of type String. Supports Accessibility? Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more information, see Accessibility . Description The specified action is defined in the Detail trigger of the button field. Because this field is not used for data input, it is usually defined as a static or control field. Tip: Uniface provides templates for command buttons that perform common actions such as retrieving and storing data, adding and removing entity occurrences, and more. By default, the CommandButton follows the Windows look and feel. If the Representation property is set to Uniface or Header , the appearance is different. For more information, see UnifaceButton and HeaderButton . Related Links Defining Command Buttons Command buttons enable the user to perform specific actions. They should only be used in form components, not in reports. KeyPadEnterAccess Specifies whether the keypad Enter key is routed through the keyboard translation table for command buttons. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}